# MVP Experiment Result Summary

The Smart Campus Event Hub prototype was tested with 5 students from Rangsit University to evaluate whether users could discover campus events, search activities, view event details, register for events, and understand reminder features.

The results showed that most users successfully completed the main tasks without assistance. The highest-performing features were the homepage, event listing, and calendar view, where users rated the clarity between 4 and 5 out of 5.

However, some usability issues were identified. Users suggested improving filter category labels, making the registration button more visible, and providing clearer instructions for reminder notifications.

Based on the experiment results, the team will improve the user interface and navigation flow before final prototype implementation.
